Video: Tennessee Williams Tribute Group Prepares for Theatre Competition

[bitsontherun GVeLPjd2]

COLUMBUS, Miss. (WCBI) – A local Tennessee Williams tribute group is getting ready for a state theatre competition this week.

And there was no better way to prepare than to perform three shows for Columbus residents at the Mississippi University for Women, Sunday.

They performed “Kingdom of Earth,” which was written by Williams.

The tribute committee will perform this play at the Mississippi Theatre Association competition this Friday in Vicksburg.

Money raised from Sunday’s performances will help cover traveling expenses to the competition.
